      "side": 1,
      "message": "As a general comment, reflecting on the Doctor use cases and requirements, I would like to mention here that Ceilometer is not intended to be a monitoring solution. It captures events and polls the infrastructure for usage data, which can then be used for mostly billing purposes or analyzing usage trends in the system.\n\nThis module consumes events that were emitted by other projects in OpenStack and uses the underlying message queue for this. Ceilometer does not deal with delays on AMQP and also does not verify the state of the system in any sense. Which means, if an update event is lost, for exapmle if an instance went to error state, you will not get notified about this, as Ceilometer does not maintain this state information.\n\nAlso using the term immadiate can be misleading here, as you will not get alarm immediately, as the event occured, but only when Ceilometer gets informed about it, which completely depends on the other services and the message queue system.",
